 lost. As far as I'm concerned, all boys schools should be banned for the damage they do. Maybe it's different for girls - all they need to do to get laid is spend a bit of time on a treadmill and wear a short skirt, but for boys, social interaction with women is all about practice. You decide. Do you want your boys to become awkward geeks or well rounded individuals. &#10;As for public vs private, I haven't decided yet. Your average public school is crap, your costly private schools are full of brats with golden spoons stuck up their asses, so both of those are out. That leaves your better public schools, which means either learning Afrikaans or moving to the northern suburbs, and your cheaper private schools which need to be judged one by one. I'll decide one day. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1080" language="en" documentId="4688" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Drunkard #1" date="08-02-2011 11:44 AM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://mybroadband.co.za/vb/showthread.php/302963-Public-school-or-private-school-for-your-kid/page1" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4688" notes="" title="Public school or private school for your kid?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="678"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="679" end="1080"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>